"Don't waste your time making dyes."

On the contrary...it is a great way to make money. I've made tons.

You need decent brewing (or alchemy) and pottery.  Go to the Lighthouse in Gunthak (zone off Stoneburnt).  There is a female merchant there (last name Brohat I think).  Buy the top four things in her inventory.  The crystal-thing and the jar go in a brew barrel.  Combine the vial and the sheet of metal in a kiln.  Then take those two results and combine them in a brew barrel and you get Prismatic dye.

They cost about 30p to make but sell for 45p on Lanys.  And they are still a hot seller.

And as the previous poster mentioned, anyone can dye their own armor without fear of failure.  They just need the LoY expansion.  There are seven slots you can dye and it takes one vial of Dye to change one slot. Be careful and make sure you have the colors you want.  Once you hit Save Dye you'll have to use another vial to change the color again.  

And it's more of a tint than a complete dye.  I have a yellow robe, but if I dye it blue it looks green. (You can test the colors all you like as long as you don't hit the Save button.)

So as long as you aren't on Lanys, make dye, sell it in the Bazaar, and make money!


